'''Utkir Yusupov''' ({{langx|uz|Oʻtkir Yusupov}}, {{langx|ru|Уткир Юсупов}}; born 4 January 1991) is an Uzbek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Uzbekistan Super League]] club [[FC Navbahor|Navbahor]]. Born in Kazakhstan, he plays for the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

==Career==
Born in Kazakhstan, Yusupov moved to Uzbekistan aged 5, and gained Uzbekistani citizenship in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2026/jun/04/world-cup-2026-complete-player-guide|title=World Cup 2026: guide to all 1,248 players|first1=Marcus|last1=Christenson|first2=David|last2=Hills|first3=Steven|last3=Bloor|first4=Garry|last4=Blight|first5=Billy|last5=Munday|date=4 June 2026|via=The Guardian}}</ref> He was included in [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]]'s squad for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]] in the United Arab Emirates.<ref name="AFC">{{cite web |url=http://www.the-afc.com/afc/documents/PdfFiles/afc-asian-cup-uae-2019-complete-squad-lists |title=AFC Asian Cup UAE 2019 Complete Squad Lists |website=the-AFC.com |publisher=[[Asian Football Confederation]] |format=PDF |date=27 December 2018 |access-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228174458/http://www.the-afc.com/afc/documents/PdfFiles/afc-asian-cup-uae-2019-complete-squad-lists |archive-date=28 December 2018}}</ref> He participated in the 2023 AFC Asian Cup in Qatar as well.

